          <td valign="top">

<span class="txth1">buflist : Buffer browser</span> 

<br>
<br>

<!-- karma table -->
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="1" bordercolor="#000066">
<tr>
  <td class="lightbg"><b>&nbsp;script karma&nbsp;</b></td>
  <td>
    Rating <b>33/15</b>,
    Downloaded by 1412  </td>
  <td class="lightbg">
  <b>&nbsp;Comments, bugs, improvements&nbsp;</b>
  </td>
  <td>
    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Script:1011">Vim wiki</a>
  </td>  
</tr>
</table>
<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=1883">Fabien Bouleau</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td>The buffer browser plugin provides you an easy way to switch from a buffer to another. The layout has been inspired on the taglist script.<br><br>Press the &lt;F4&gt; key to toggle the buffer list on and off. Help can be displayed by pressing the 'h' key. <br><br>General keymaps:<br><br>- &lt;S-F3&gt;/&lt;S-F4&gt; to decrease/increase window height by 1<br>- &lt;C-S-F3&gt;/&lt;C-S-F4&gt; to decrease/increase window height by 5<br><br>Usage when not in buffer list:<br><br>- &lt;F4&gt; to open/access buffer list panel<br>- \\0 to \\9 to mark window with number<br>- \\p to mark window as preview window<br><br>Usage when in buffer list:<br><br>- h to toggle help<br>- q to close buffer list (same as CTRL-W q)<br>- p to preview file in preview window<br>- d to delete currently selected buffer<br>- u to update buffer list<br>- x to toggle path display<br>- s to toggle sorting by buffer number/name/extension<br>- n/N to edit file in new window below/above &lt;F4&gt; <br>- &lt;CR&gt; to edit file in last window visited before &lt;F4&gt;<br>- \\0 to \\9 to edit file in window marked 0 to 9<br>- &lt;F4&gt; to go back to &lt;F4&gt; window<br>- &lt;S-F3&gt; to decrease buffer list width by 1<br>- &lt;S-F4&gt; to increase buffer list width by 1<br>- &lt;C-S-F3&gt; to decrease buffer list width by 5<br>- &lt;C-S-F4&gt; to increase buffer list width by 5<br><br>Remark: the \ is in fact defined as &lt;Leader&gt;, it might thus change regarding your environment settings.<br><br>Change log:<br><br>From 1.6 to 1.7:<br><br>- g:BufList_Hide set to 1 or 0 whether the buflist panel shall be respectively hidden or not once buffer is selected (&lt;CR&gt; key).<br>- Copy buffer no longer erased when buffer is selected or when panel is updated.<br><br>From 1.5 to 1.6:<br><br>- buffer path display bug fix<br>- nonumber set for buffer list (thanks to Ian)<br>- &lt;C-S-F3&gt;/&lt;C-S-F4&gt; for increasing/decreasing window size<br></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td>Copy the buflist.vim file into your $VIM/vimfiles/plugin directory and restart VIM</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

